    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-10-30T21:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-10-30T21:00:00-05:00" n="212"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d212">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">853M.77/25: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Consul at Loanda, Angola</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Day</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-10-30T22:00:00-04:00"
                            >October 30, 1942—10 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>11. Your 5, October 26, midnight.</p>
                <quote rend="blockquote">
                    <p>“The Department agrees in principle with the proposals made by the Portuguese
                        Minister of Colonies, whose interest in the matter is appreciated, regarding
                        the use by American Government Agencies of the Benguela Railroad, which
                        subject was already under discussion here on the basis of information
                        transmitted by the War Department. Since it is preferable for negotiations
                        of this character with foreign governments to be handled by representatives
                        of this Department, plans have already been made to expedite the travel of
                        Consul General Linnell to Loanda to enter into discussions on this subject
                        with the Minister of Colonies.”</p>
                </quote>
                <p>A separate instruction will follow regarding cable charges.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
